<td align="center">
<div class="poemtitle">Molokai Budget Vacation</div> 
<br>
<a class="byline" href="javascript:goauthor('wright')">by Kirby Wright</a> <br>
<br>
<br>
<table cellpadding="20" cellspacing="0"><tr><td>
The lawn is full<br>
Of weeds and stumps.<br>
<br>
Trees have been<br>
Beheaded here.<br>
<br>
Two dogs sniff<br>
An eel carcass?<br>
<br>
They choose sides,<br>
Stretch it like rubber.<br>
<br>
The smell of death<br>
Defeats the gardenias.<br>
<br>
My plywood shack<br>
Overlooks a harbor<br>
<br>
Stuffed with lobster shells<br>
And liquor bottles.<br>
<br>
The beach east<br>
Is thin and beige.<br>
<br>
The shallows to the west?<br>
A minefield of sting rays.<BR>
</td>
<td align="right"><img src="images/molokaibudgetvacation.jpg"><br><span class="byartist">Patricia Wallace Jones</span></td>
</tr></table>
</td>
</tr>
